15/07/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Two Montenegrin citizens who had just landed at Tirana Airport were robbed on Wednesday (July 14th) by masked gunmen. Police say one of the victims was transferred to the hospital in Lezha with injuries. The gunmen reportedly ran off with about 16,000 euros and the victims' personal belongings. The two Montenegrins had just arrived from the United States. (Lajmifundit, Ora News, Balkan Web - 14/07/10)
